data.description: Looking for privacy? Looking for a place to make your very own secluded sanctuary surrounded by nature? Need space to spread out? Come and take a look at this property that offers 5 acres in Webster at the end of a dead-end road with limited neighbors giving you plenty of privacy and seclusion.  You have plenty of room to put in a pool and bring your toys to play. Need RV parking? Need boat parking? Look no further. Want to grow your own food? Have a vegetable garden or create a beautiful flower garden ~ this is a place to let loose your creativity. Want to have chickens? Look no further!  This property has its own well and septic. The property currently has a manufactured home with 3 bedrooms and 2 baths and 2 porches to enjoy the surrounding seclusion, the privacy and the view surrounded by trees and a family of deer as you sip your first cup of joe in the early morning light. Or take a load off as you enjoy a cold brew as after a hard day of work. Not gonna sugar coated ~ this home NEEDS some TLC ~ the home has a new roof was installed in 2020. The ac is working, and the home does come with range, dishwasher, and refrigerator. There is floor damage in the kitchen that will need to be repaired in order to have a fully functioning kitchen area~ the home could use some updating and remodeling, or you have the option to have the manufactured home removed and start from scratch if you wanted to build your very own custom home or replace it with a newer manufactured home ~ you have lots of options and endless possibilities with this property. This property offers a lot of privacy, seclusion, and space yet it is close to US 301 and an EZ commute to I75 and is centrally located to Tampa, Ocala & Orlando ~ a hop and skip away from major shopping and dining. And let’s not forget the World-Famous Webster Flea Market. Love the outdoors ~ you are close to many fishing, boating & kayaking spots from Silver Lake to Hog’s Island. Want to bike, rollerblade or run, look no further than the Withlacoochee State Trail where you are within 10 minutes from one of its entry points. Looking for something with some History ~ look no further than Dade Battlefield Historic State Park where every year the reenact the battle of the Second Seminole War ~ park also has picnic area and playgrounds for the whole family to enjoy. And let us not forget this property has NO HOA or CDD with lots of privacy! Come and check it out! Being Sold As-Is with right to inspect.
